\begin{equation\*}
I(x) \approx g(t_0) \sqrt{\frac{2}{\pi}} e^{-x^2/2}
\end{equation\*}
Finally, we substitute back $t_0$ to get:
\begin{align\*}
I(x) &\approx g(t_0) \sqrt{\frac{2}{\pi}} e^{-x^2/2} \\
&= (1.1 t_0^5+2.0 t_0^3+2.5 \sin{\left(t_0 \right)}) \sqrt{\frac{2}{\pi}} e^{-x^2/2}
\end{align\*}
